Preheat the oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Chop @potatoes{600%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then into 1cm chips (peeling optional).

On a lined #baking tray{}, toss with @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste} and a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Spread out in a single layer. Cook on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn the tray halfway through.

When ~{5%minutes} of cooking time remain, push the chips together and scatter over the @grated cheese{50%g}. Cook for the remaining time, allowing the cheese to melt.

Meanwhile, pick the @rosemary{1%sprig} leaves from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks).

Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(thinly sliced).

Trim the @carrot{2}(trimmed), then halve lengthways (no need to peel). Chop into 1cm wide, 5cm long batons.

Pop the carrots onto a large (lined) baking tray.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste}, season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

Roast on the middle shelf of the oven until tender, ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn the tray halfway through cooking.

In a large #bowl{}, mix @rosemary{1}(roughly chopped), @Irish pork mince{240%g}, garlic, @breadcrumbs{1%pack}, 2 tbsp @water{2%tbsp} (per 2P) and @salt{1/4%tsp} (per 2P).

Season with @pepper{to taste} and mix together by hand. Roll into evenly-sized balls, 3-4 per person.

Pop onto a (separate) lined baking tray.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw mince. Meatballs are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Bake on the top shelf of the oven until browned outside and cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, place a #pan{} over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once hot, add the onion and fry until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Stir in the @red wine jus{1%sachet} and @cranberry chutney{1%sachet}.

Allow the sauce to bubble and thicken, stirring regularly, ~{2-3%minutes}.

When the meatballs are cooked through, add them to the sauce and toss to coat.

> TIP: Loosen the sauce with a splash of water if you feel it's too thick.

Share the cheesy chips and roasted carrot between plates.

Serve the meatballs and sauce alongside.